<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-24T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-24T23:00:00-05:00" n="255" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d255">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1070.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-24T23:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your February 21, 3 p.m. Your telegram will be laid before the
                            President.</p>
                        <p>To what extent have the alleged irregularities of Arias and Vidal
                            interfered with the fulfilment of the terms of the Convention? If
                            evidence is such as to cause Dominican Government to proclaim Arias or
                            Vidal or both as offenders against the law, how soon after such
                            proclamation does Bordas believe constitutional amendments and
                            legislative reforms could be enacted and what would be the character and
                            extent of material assistance required by Constituted Government?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>